==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Black art
<hw>Black" art`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>The art practiced by conjurers
and witches; necromancy; conjuration; magic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This name was given in the Middle Ages to necromancy,
under the idea that the latter term was derived from <ets>niger</ets>
black, instead of <grk>nekro`s</grk>, a dead person, and
<grk>mantei`a</grk>, divination. <rj><au>Wright.</au></rj> </note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Black-a-vised</ent>⟦br⟧
